TITLE: Correct Project & Folder Structure (CRITICAL)

Your system MUST look like this:

ROOT FOLDER (example: htdocs)
│
├── cinema-api
│   ├── app/
│   ├── config/
│   ├── routes/
│   ├── database/
│   ├── .env
│   └── artisan
│
└── cinema-frontend
    ├── src/
    ├── public/
    ├── node_modules/
    ├── package.json
    └── README.md

RULES:
- Laravel lives in cinema-api
- React lives in cinema-frontend
- They NEVER go inside each other

WHY THIS MATTERS:
Each project has:
- Its own server
- Its own dependencies
- Its own startup command

Mixing them causes:
- npm errors
- missing scripts
- broken builds
